{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":973,"text":"We are built out of very small stuff,"},{"time":5516,"text":"and we are embedded in\na very large cosmos,"},{"time":8031,"text":"and the fact is that we are not\nvery good at understanding reality"},{"time":12582,"text":"at either of those scales,"},{"time":14161,"text":"and that's because our brains"},{"time":15763,"text":"haven't evolved to understand \nthe world at that scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":20157,"text":"Instead, we're trapped on this\nvery thin slice of perception"},{"time":24377,"text":"right in the middle."},{"time":26723,"text":"But it gets strange, because even at \nthat slice of reality that we call home,"},{"time":31191,"text":"we're not seeing most\nof the action that's going on."},{"time":34176,"text":"So take the colors of our world."},{"time":37566,"text":"This is light waves, electromagnetic\nradiation that bounces off objects"},{"time":42279,"text":"and it hits specialized receptors\nin the back of our eyes."},{"time":45716,"text":"But we're not seeing\nall the waves out there."},{"time":49361,"text":"In fact, what we see"},{"time":51056,"text":"is less than a 10 trillionth\nof what's out there."},{"time":55119,"text":"So you have radio waves and microwaves"},{"time":58486,"text":"and X-rays and gamma rays\npassing through your body right now"},{"time":61783,"text":"and you're completely unaware of it,"},{"time":64732,"text":"because you don't come with\nthe proper biological receptors"},{"time":67913,"text":"for picking it up."},{"time":69631,"text":"There are thousands\nof cell phone conversations"},{"time":72198,"text":"passing through you right now,"},{"time":73754,"text":"and you're utterly blind to it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76055,"text":"Now, it's not that these things\nare inherently unseeable."},{"time":79953,"text":"Snakes include some infrared\nin their reality,"},{"time":84852,"text":"and honeybees include ultraviolet\nin their view of the world,"},{"time":88730,"text":"and of course we build machines\nin the dashboards of our cars"},{"time":91655,"text":"to pick up on signals\nin the radio frequency range,"},{"time":94883,"text":"and we built machines in hospitals\nto pick up on the X-ray range."},{"time":98575,"text":"But you can't sense\nany of those by yourself,"},{"time":101965,"text":"at least not yet,"},{"time":103474,"text":"because you don't come equipped\nwith the proper sensors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107421,"text":"Now, what this means is that\nour experience of reality"},{"time":111902,"text":"is constrained by our biology,"},{"time":115362,"text":"and that goes against\nthe common sense notion"},{"time":117916,"text":"that our eyes and our ears\nand our fingertips"},{"time":120179,"text":"are just picking up\nthe objective reality that's out there."},{"time":124394,"text":"Instead, our brains are sampling\njust a little bit of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130013,"text":"Now, across the animal kingdom,"},{"time":132080,"text":"different animals pick up\non different parts of reality."},{"time":135400,"text":"So in the blind\nand deaf world of the tick,"},{"time":138349,"text":"the important signals\nare temperature and butyric acid;"},{"time":142830,"text":"in the world of the black ghost knifefish,"},{"time":145756,"text":"its sensory world is lavishly colored\nby electrical fields;"},{"time":150655,"text":"and for the echolocating bat,"},{"time":153116,"text":"its reality is constructed\nout of air compression waves."},{"time":157156,"text":"That's the slice of their ecosystem\nthat they can pick up on,"},{"time":161521,"text":"and we have a word for this in science."},{"time":163403,"text":"It's called the umwelt,"},{"time":164911,"text":"which is the German word\nfor the surrounding world."},{"time":168603,"text":"Now, presumably, every animal assumes"},{"time":171598,"text":"that its umwelt is the entire\nobjective reality out there,"},{"time":175987,"text":"because why would you ever stop to imagine"},{"time":178281,"text":"that there's something beyond\nwhat we can sense."},{"time":181412,"text":"Instead, what we all do\nis we accept reality"},{"time":184126,"text":"as it's presented to us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187222,"text":"Let's do a consciousness-raiser on this."},{"time":189717,"text":"Imagine that you are a bloodhound dog."},{"time":192973,"text":"Your whole world is about smelling."},{"time":195178,"text":"You've got a long snout that has\n200 million scent receptors in it,"},{"time":199590,"text":"and you have wet nostrils\nthat attract and trap scent molecules,"},{"time":204094,"text":"and your nostrils even have slits\nso you can take big nosefuls of air."},{"time":208088,"text":"Everything is about smell for you."},{"time":211362,"text":"So one day, you stop in your tracks\nwith a revelation."},{"time":215263,"text":"You look at your human owner\nand you think,"},{"time":218583,"text":"\"What is it like to have the pitiful,\nimpoverished nose of a human?"},{"time":223393,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":225083,"text":"What is it like when you take\na feeble little noseful of air?"},{"time":228335,"text":"How can you not know that there's\na cat 100 yards away,"},{"time":232384,"text":"or that your neighbor was on\nthis very spot six hours ago?\""},{"time":235718,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":238458,"text":"So because we're humans,"},{"time":240757,"text":"we've never experienced\nthat world of smell,"},{"time":243404,"text":"so we don't miss it,"},{"time":246083,"text":"because we are firmly settled\ninto our umwelt."},{"time":250114,"text":"But the question is,\ndo we have to be stuck there?"},{"time":254317,"text":"So as a neuroscientist, I'm interested\nin the way that technology"},{"time":258845,"text":"might expand our umwelt,"},{"time":261468,"text":"and how that's going to change\nthe experience of being human."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266228,"text":"So we already know that we can marry\nour technology to our biology,"},{"time":269781,"text":"because there are hundreds of thousands\nof people walking around"},{"time":273565,"text":"with artificial hearing\nand artificial vision."},{"time":277164,"text":"So the way this works is, you take\na microphone and you digitize the signal,"},{"time":281553,"text":"and you put an electrode strip\ndirectly into the inner ear."},{"time":285291,"text":"Or, with the retinal implant,\nyou take a camera"},{"time":287590,"text":"and you digitize the signal,\nand then you plug an electrode grid"},{"time":290864,"text":"directly into the optic nerve."},{"time":293882,"text":"And as recently as 15 years ago,"},{"time":297806,"text":"there were a lot of scientists who thought\nthese technologies wouldn't work."},{"time":301544,"text":"Why? It's because these technologies\nspeak the language of Silicon Valley,"},{"time":306723,"text":"and it's not exactly the same dialect\nas our natural biological sense organs."},{"time":312295,"text":"But the fact is that it works;"},{"time":314710,"text":"the brain figures out\nhow to use the signals just fine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319719,"text":"Now, how do we understand that?"},{"time":321763,"text":"Well, here's the big secret:"},{"time":323458,"text":"Your brain is not hearing\nor seeing any of this."},{"time":328728,"text":"Your brain is locked in a vault of silence\nand darkness inside your skull."},{"time":335183,"text":"All it ever sees are\nelectrochemical signals"},{"time":338991,"text":"that come in along different data cables,"},{"time":341540,"text":"and this is all it has to work with,\nand nothing more."},{"time":346672,"text":"Now, amazingly,"},{"time":348924,"text":"the brain is really good\nat taking in these signals"},{"time":351687,"text":"and extracting patterns\nand assigning meaning,"},{"time":355238,"text":"so that it takes this inner cosmos\nand puts together a story"},{"time":359292,"text":"of this, your subjective world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364179,"text":"But here's the key point:"},{"time":366129,"text":"Your brain doesn't know,\nand it doesn't care,"},{"time":369519,"text":"where it gets the data from."},{"time":372561,"text":"Whatever information comes in,\nit just figures out what to do with it."},{"time":377414,"text":"And this is a very efficient\nkind of machine."},{"time":379852,"text":"It's essentially a general purpose\ncomputing device,"},{"time":384008,"text":"and it just takes in everything"},{"time":386423,"text":"and figures out\nwhat it's going to do with it,"},{"time":389023,"text":"and that, I think, frees up Mother Nature"},{"time":392669,"text":"to tinker around with different\nsorts of input channels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397452,"text":"So I call this the P.H. \nmodel of evolution,"},{"time":400284,"text":"and I don't want to get\ntoo technical here,"},{"time":402328,"text":"but P.H. stands for Potato Head,"},{"time":405369,"text":"and I use this name to emphasize\nthat all these sensors"},{"time":409200,"text":"that we know and love, like our eyes\nand our ears and our fingertips,"},{"time":412451,"text":"these are merely peripheral\nplug-and-play devices:"},{"time":416770,"text":"You stick them in, and you're good to go."},{"time":420044,"text":"The brain figures out what to do\nwith the data that comes in."},{"time":426243,"text":"And when you look across\nthe animal kingdom,"},{"time":428449,"text":"you find lots of peripheral devices."},{"time":431096,"text":"So snakes have heat pits\nwith which to detect infrared,"},{"time":435206,"text":"and the ghost knifefish has\nelectroreceptors,"},{"time":438456,"text":"and the star-nosed mole has this appendage"},{"time":441057,"text":"with 22 fingers on it"},{"time":443704,"text":"with which it feels around and constructs\na 3D model of the world,"},{"time":447373,"text":"and many birds have magnetite\nso they can orient"},{"time":451297,"text":"to the magnetic field of the planet."},{"time":453792,"text":"So what this means is that\nnature doesn't have to continually"},{"time":457664,"text":"redesign the brain."},{"time":460079,"text":"Instead, with the principles\nof brain operation established,"},{"time":464560,"text":"all nature has to worry about\nis designing new peripherals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469239,"text":"Okay. So what this means is this:"},{"time":472164,"text":"The lesson that surfaces"},{"time":474184,"text":"is that there's nothing\nreally special or fundamental"},{"time":477853,"text":"about the biology that we\ncome to the table with."},{"time":480848,"text":"It's just what we have inherited"},{"time":482915,"text":"from a complex road of evolution."},{"time":486142,"text":"But it's not what we have to stick with,"},{"time":489671,"text":"and our best proof of principle of this"},{"time":491715,"text":"comes from what's called\nsensory substitution."},{"time":494315,"text":"And that refers to feeding\ninformation into the brain"},{"time":497543,"text":"via unusual sensory channels,"},{"time":500329,"text":"and the brain just figures out\nwhat to do with it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503208,"text":"Now, that might sound speculative,"},{"time":505669,"text":"but the first paper demonstrating this was\npublished in the journal Nature in 1969."},{"time":511985,"text":"So a scientist named Paul Bach-y-Rita"},{"time":514353,"text":"put blind people\nin a modified dental chair,"},{"time":517581,"text":"and he set up a video feed,"},{"time":519926,"text":"and he put something\nin front of the camera,"},{"time":522178,"text":"and then you would feel that"},{"time":524639,"text":"poked into your back\nwith a grid of solenoids."},{"time":527565,"text":"So if you wiggle a coffee cup\nin front of the camera,"},{"time":530049,"text":"you're feeling that in your back,"},{"time":532394,"text":"and amazingly, blind people\ngot pretty good"},{"time":535482,"text":"at being able to determine\nwhat was in front of the camera"},{"time":539035,"text":"just by feeling it\nin the small of their back."},{"time":542820,"text":"Now, there have been many\nmodern incarnations of this."},{"time":546326,"text":"The sonic glasses take a video feed\nright in front of you"},{"time":549600,"text":"and turn that into a sonic landscape,"},{"time":552455,"text":"so as things move around,\nand get closer and farther,"},{"time":554956,"text":"it sounds like \"Bzz, bzz, bzz.\""},{"time":557030,"text":"It sounds like a cacophony,"},{"time":559003,"text":"but after several weeks, blind people\nstart getting pretty good"},{"time":562997,"text":"at understanding what's in front of them"},{"time":565319,"text":"just based on what they're hearing."},{"time":567966,"text":"And it doesn't have to be\nthrough the ears:"},{"time":569990,"text":"this system uses an electrotactile grid\non the forehead,"},{"time":573354,"text":"so whatever's in front of the video feed,\nyou're feeling it on your forehead."},{"time":577044,"text":"Why the forehead? Because you're not\nusing it for much else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579897,"text":"The most modern incarnation\nis called the brainport,"},{"time":584103,"text":"and this is a little electrogrid\nthat sits on your tongue,"},{"time":587852,"text":"and the video feed gets turned into\nthese little electrotactile signals,"},{"time":591968,"text":"and blind people get so good at using this\nthat they can throw a ball into a basket,"},{"time":598455,"text":"or they can navigate\ncomplex obstacle courses."},{"time":603311,"text":"They can come to see through their tongue."},{"time":607525,"text":"Now, that sounds completely insane, right?"},{"time":609731,"text":"But remember, all vision ever is"},{"time":612540,"text":"is electrochemical signals\ncoursing around in your brain."},{"time":616557,"text":"Your brain doesn't know\nwhere the signals come from."},{"time":619251,"text":"It just figures out what to do with them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622687,"text":"So my interest in my lab\nis sensory substitution for the deaf,"},{"time":628493,"text":"and this is a project I've undertaken"},{"time":631232,"text":"with a graduate student\nin my lab, Scott Novich,"},{"time":634227,"text":"who is spearheading this for his thesis."},{"time":636526,"text":"And here is what we wanted to do:"},{"time":638522,"text":"we wanted to make it so that\nsound from the world gets converted"},{"time":642516,"text":"in some way so that a deaf person\ncan understand what is being said."},{"time":647392,"text":"And we wanted to do this, given the power\nand ubiquity of portable computing,"},{"time":651920,"text":"we wanted to make sure that this\nwould run on cell phones and tablets,"},{"time":656796,"text":"and also we wanted\nto make this a wearable,"},{"time":659094,"text":"something that you could wear\nunder your clothing."},{"time":662136,"text":"So here's the concept."},{"time":665326,"text":"So as I'm speaking, my sound\nis getting captured by the tablet,"},{"time":670402,"text":"and then it's getting mapped onto a vest\nthat's covered in vibratory motors,"},{"time":676160,"text":"just like the motors in your cell phone."},{"time":679597,"text":"So as I'm speaking,"},{"time":681988,"text":"the sound is getting translated\nto a pattern of vibration on the vest."},{"time":688327,"text":"Now, this is not just conceptual:"},{"time":689906,"text":"this tablet is transmitting Bluetooth,\nand I'm wearing the vest right now."},{"time":695014,"text":"So as I'm speaking -- (Applause) --"},{"time":698033,"text":"the sound is getting translated\ninto dynamic patterns of vibration."},{"time":703966,"text":"I'm feeling the sonic world around me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709340,"text":"So, we've been testing this\nwith deaf people now,"},{"time":713404,"text":"and it turns out that after\njust a little bit of time,"},{"time":716910,"text":"people can start feeling,\nthey can start understanding"},{"time":720300,"text":"the language of the vest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":722970,"text":"So this is Jonathan. He's 37 years old.\nHe has a master's degree."},{"time":727753,"text":"He was born profoundly deaf,"},{"time":730098,"text":"which means that there's a part\nof his umwelt that's unavailable to him."},{"time":734208,"text":"So we had Jonathan train with the vest\nfor four days, two hours a day,"},{"time":738596,"text":"and here he is on the fifth day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741876,"text":"Scott Novich: You."}]},{"cues":[{"time":744012,"text":"David Eagleman: So Scott says a word,\nJonathan feels it on the vest,"},{"time":747226,"text":"and he writes it on the board."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750282,"text":"SN: Where. Where."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754168,"text":"DE: Jonathan is able to translate\nthis complicated pattern of vibrations"},{"time":757805,"text":"into an understanding\nof what's being said."}]},{"cues":[{"time":760684,"text":"SN: Touch. Touch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":764283,"text":"DE: Now, he's not doing this --"},{"time":768723,"text":"(Applause) --"},{"time":775944,"text":"Jonathan is not doing this consciously,\nbecause the patterns are too complicated,"},{"time":780030,"text":"but his brain is starting to unlock\nthe pattern that allows it to figure out"},{"time":785510,"text":"what the data mean,"},{"time":787786,"text":"and our expectation is that,\nafter wearing this for about three months,"},{"time":791988,"text":"he will have a direct\nperceptual experience of hearing"},{"time":796586,"text":"in the same way that when a blind person\npasses a finger over braille,"},{"time":800765,"text":"the meaning comes directly off the page\nwithout any conscious intervention at all."},{"time":806941,"text":"Now, this technology has the potential\nto be a game-changer,"},{"time":810494,"text":"because the only other solution\nfor deafness is a cochlear implant,"},{"time":814278,"text":"and that requires an invasive surgery."},{"time":817181,"text":"And this can be built for 40 times cheaper\nthan a cochlear implant,"},{"time":822335,"text":"which opens up this technology globally,\neven for the poorest countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":828052,"text":"Now, we've been very encouraged\nby our results with sensory substitution,"},{"time":833171,"text":"but what we've been thinking a lot about\nis sensory addition."},{"time":837374,"text":"How could we use a technology like this\nto add a completely new kind of sense,"},{"time":842803,"text":"to expand the human umvelt?"},{"time":845937,"text":"For example, could we feed\nreal-time data from the Internet"},{"time":850186,"text":"directly into somebody's brain,"},{"time":852067,"text":"and can they develop a direct\nperceptual experience?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":855945,"text":"So here's an experiment\nwe're doing in the lab."},{"time":858482,"text":"A subject is feeling a real-time\nstreaming feed from the Net of data"},{"time":862376,"text":"for five seconds."},{"time":864187,"text":"Then, two buttons appear,\nand he has to make a choice."},{"time":867456,"text":"He doesn't know what's going on."},{"time":869145,"text":"He makes a choice,\nand he gets feedback after one second."},{"time":871841,"text":"Now, here's the thing:"},{"time":873046,"text":"The subject has no idea\nwhat all the patterns mean,"},{"time":875690,"text":"but we're seeing if he gets better\nat figuring out which button to press."},{"time":879361,"text":"He doesn't know that what we're feeding"},{"time":881428,"text":"is real-time data from the stock market,"},{"time":884609,"text":"and he's making buy and sell decisions."},{"time":887116,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":889490,"text":"And the feedback is telling him\nwhether he did the right thing or not."},{"time":892792,"text":"And what we're seeing is,\ncan we expand the human umvelt"},{"time":895661,"text":"so that he comes to have,\nafter several weeks,"},{"time":898656,"text":"a direct perceptual experience\nof the economic movements of the planet."},{"time":904763,"text":"So we'll report on that later\nto see how well this goes."},{"time":908129,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":910730,"text":"Here's another thing we're doing:"},{"time":912820,"text":"During the talks this morning,\nwe've been automatically scraping Twitter"},{"time":917417,"text":"for the TED2015 hashtag,"},{"time":919855,"text":"and we've been doing\nan automated sentiment analysis,"},{"time":922548,"text":"which means, are people using positive\nwords or negative words or neutral?"},{"time":927123,"text":"And while this has been going on,"},{"time":929567,"text":"I have been feeling this,"},{"time":932562,"text":"and so I am plugged in\nto the aggregate emotion"},{"time":936835,"text":"of thousands of people in real time,"},{"time":940991,"text":"and that's a new kind of human experience,\nbecause now I can know"},{"time":944729,"text":"how everyone's doing\nand how much you're loving this."},{"time":948026,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":954899,"text":"It's a bigger experience\nthan a human can normally have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":959845,"text":"We're also expanding the umvelt of pilots."},{"time":962538,"text":"So in this case, the vest is streaming\nnine different measures"},{"time":966624,"text":"from this quadcopter,"},{"time":968250,"text":"so pitch and yaw and roll\nand orientation and heading,"},{"time":971617,"text":"and that improves\nthis pilot's ability to fly it."},{"time":975703,"text":"It's essentially like he's extending\nhis skin up there, far away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":980998,"text":"And that's just the beginning."},{"time":982553,"text":"What we're envisioning is taking\na modern cockpit full of gauges"},{"time":988357,"text":"and instead of trying\nto read the whole thing, you feel it."},{"time":992908,"text":"We live in a world of information now,"},{"time":995393,"text":"and there is a difference\nbetween accessing big data"},{"time":999201,"text":"and experiencing it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1002289,"text":"So I think there's really no end\nto the possibilities"},{"time":1006114,"text":"on the horizon for human expansion."},{"time":1008436,"text":"Just imagine an astronaut\nbeing able to feel"},{"time":1013358,"text":"the overall health\nof the International Space Station,"},{"time":1016679,"text":"or, for that matter, having you feel\nthe invisible states of your own health,"},{"time":1021555,"text":"like your blood sugar\nand the state of your microbiome,"},{"time":1025494,"text":"or having 360-degree vision\nor seeing in infrared or ultraviolet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1031121,"text":"So the key is this:\nAs we move into the future,"},{"time":1034616,"text":"we're going to increasingly be able\nto choose our own peripheral devices."},{"time":1039515,"text":"We no longer have to wait\nfor Mother Nature's sensory gifts"},{"time":1043369,"text":"on her timescales,"},{"time":1045227,"text":"but instead, like any good parent,\nshe's given us the tools that we need"},{"time":1049499,"text":"to go out and define our own trajectory."},{"time":1053632,"text":"So the question now is,"},{"time":1055373,"text":"how do you want to go out\nand experience your universe?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1060598,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1062641,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1079365,"text":"Chris Anderson: Can you feel it?\nDE: Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1081553,"text":"Actually, this was the first time\nI felt applause on the vest."},{"time":1084943,"text":"It's nice. It's like a massage. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1087102,"text":"CA: Twitter's going crazy.\nTwitter's going mad."},{"time":1090747,"text":"So that stock market experiment."},{"time":1093040,"text":"This could be the first experiment\nthat secures its funding forevermore,"},{"time":1097568,"text":"right, if successful?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1099563,"text":"DE: Well, that's right, I wouldn't\nhave to write to NIH anymore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1102715,"text":"CA: Well look, just to be\nskeptical for a minute,"},{"time":1105532,"text":"I mean, this is amazing,\nbut isn't most of the evidence so far"},{"time":1108702,"text":"that sensory substitution works,"},{"time":1111049,"text":"not necessarily \nthat sensory addition works?"},{"time":1113156,"text":"I mean, isn't it possible that the\nblind person can see through their tongue"},{"time":1116793,"text":"because the visual cortex is still there,\nready to process,"},{"time":1121971,"text":"and that that is needed as part of it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1123790,"text":"DE: That's a great question.\nWe actually have no idea"},{"time":1126434,"text":"what the theoretical limits are of what\nkind of data the brain can take in."},{"time":1130330,"text":"The general story, though,\nis that it's extraordinarily flexible."},{"time":1133402,"text":"So when a person goes blind,\nwhat we used to call their visual cortex"},{"time":1137207,"text":"gets taken over by other things,\nby touch, by hearing, by vocabulary."},{"time":1142265,"text":"So what that tells us is that\nthe cortex is kind of a one-trick pony."},{"time":1146327,"text":"It just runs certain kinds\nof computations on things."},{"time":1148975,"text":"And when we look around\nat things like braille, for example,"},{"time":1152076,"text":"people are getting information\nthrough bumps on their fingers."},{"time":1155165,"text":"So I don't think we have any reason\nto think there's a theoretical limit"},{"time":1158820,"text":"that we know the edge of."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1161244,"text":"CA: If this checks out,\nyou're going to be deluged."},{"time":1164508,"text":"There are so many\npossible applications for this."},{"time":1167759,"text":"Are you ready for this? What are you most\nexcited about, the direction it might go?"},{"time":1171690,"text":"DE: I mean, I think there's\na lot of applications here."},{"time":1174267,"text":"In terms of beyond sensory substitution,\nthe things I started mentioning"},{"time":1177715,"text":"about astronauts on the space station,\nthey spend a lot of their time"},{"time":1182085,"text":"monitoring things, and they could instead\njust get what's going on,"},{"time":1185304,"text":"because what this is really good for\nis multidimensional data."},{"time":1188764,"text":"The key is this: Our visual systems\nare good at detecting blobs and edges,"},{"time":1193547,"text":"but they're really bad\nat what our world has become,"},{"time":1195995,"text":"which is screens\nwith lots and lots of data."},{"time":1198182,"text":"We have to crawl that\nwith our attentional systems."},{"time":1200585,"text":"So this is a way of just\nfeeling the state of something,"},{"time":1203255,"text":"just like the way you know the state\nof your body as you're standing around."},{"time":1206849,"text":"So I think heavy machinery, safety,\nfeeling the state of a factory,"},{"time":1210028,"text":"of your equipment, that's one place\nit'll go right away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1213092,"text":"CA: David Eagleman, that was one\nmind-blowing talk. Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1216797,"text":"DE: Thank you, Chris.\n(Applause)"}]}]}